 Johannesburg </LOCATION>. Police have released only a few details about the case and said that `` senstive'' investigations were continuing following the arrests last week. Local press reports said the suspects, all in their 20s, had targeted the owners of licensed and unlicensed taverns in the townships and had stolen at least $ 40,000 over a four-month period. The constables reportedly told their victims they were members of the White Wolves, a name which has surfaced in recent months in connection with acts of terror by white right-wing extremists. Police officials have insisted there is no evidence the White Wolves actually exists.
