<HEAD>Thunderstorms Drench Kansas, East Coast</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Showers and thunderstorms drenched sections of <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION> and much of the <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Seaboard </LOCATION> on Sunday, and rain fell on much of the rest of the nation. Low-temperature records were tied in three Southern cities. Downpours in southwest <LOCATION> Kansas </LOCATION> overnight dumped more than 4 inches of rain at <LOCATION> Coldwater </LOCATION> and Offerle. Light rain continued into the afternoon. Scattered showers and thunderstorms hit much of the <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION>, with the heaviest rain over <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> and southern <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>. Up to 3 inches of rain soaked <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> in the 24 hours ending at midafternoon Sunday. Thunderstorms also extended from northern <LOCATION> Oklahoma </LOCATION> to west-central <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, and over the northern Plains and upper <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Myers </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla. </LOCATION>, tied its record low for the date at 70 degrees; <LOCATION> Meridian </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Miss. </LOCATION>, tied its 62-degree record and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Orleans </LOCATION> tied its 68-degree mark. Temperatures around the nation at 3 p.m. EDT ranged from 59 degrees at <LOCATION> Lompoc </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, to 107 in Needles and <LOCATION> Palm </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Springs </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>. Sunday's low for the Lower 48 states was 30 degrees at <LOCATION> Truckee </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>. Monday's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms from the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> states to the Great Lakes region and northern <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION> states; and scattered showers and thunderstorms from <LOCATION> Montana </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION> and Highs in the 60s and 70s were predicted along the <LOCATION> Pacific </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Coast </LOCATION>, in the 70s from the upper <LOCATION> Mississippi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Valley </LOCATION> to northern <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>, in the lower 90s across southern <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> and southern <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> and west of the <LOCATION> Rockies </LOCATION> and above 100 degrees in the desert Southwest.
