<HEAD>Spokesman Says PLO Agrees To Elections If They End Israeli Occupation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> said Sunday the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> is ready for elections in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION> if it is guaranteed the balloting will end <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> occupation of the territories. `` I hereby announce that the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> is ready for elections tomorrow if it is guaranteed freedom and democracy,'' said <PERSON> Bassam </PERSON> <PERSON> Abu </PERSON> <PERSON> Sharif </PERSON>, a spokesman for <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> chairman <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>, told the <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> `` We are ready if the world community will guarantee that the elections we go to will be one step in a process that will lead to an end of the <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> occupation of the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION>,'' he said in the interview in <LOCATION> Tunisia </LOCATION>, where <ORGANIZATION> Fatah </ORGANIZATION>, the main group in the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, held its congress last week. The congress called for intensified military action to end the <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> occupation of the territories and rejected Israeli Premier <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s plan for elections. `` What we are after is freedom, like any other people,'' <PERSON> Sharif </PERSON> said. `` We are asking the Israelis to come and sit down and talk to us.'' But he said that as long as <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> occupies the territories the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> will continue to lead the uprising in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>. More than 530 Palestinians and 38 Israelis have been killed in the uprising that began in December 1987. <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> has proposed elections in the occupied lands and talks with the elected Palestinian representatives on an interim self-rule solution for the 1.7 million Arabs in the territories. In <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>, an Israeli government official, speaking on condition of anonymity, said he saw nothing new in <PERSON> Abu </PERSON> <PERSON> Sharif </PERSON>'s statement He said the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>'s repeated demand for guaranteeing creation of a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> state before any negotiations amounts to rejection of <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s call for talks without conditions.
